   {
      "body" : "The memset makes little sense to me. `pch` points to caller-allocated memory. It's up to the caller to securely erase the passed-in memory before deallocating it - irrespective of whether it ended with an error. Secure erasing the caller's memory is not the responsibility of the serialization system. If it was local state that would otherwise linger around I could understand.",
      "created_at" : "2014-08-19T10:12:05Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/4618#issuecomment-52614031",
      "id" : 52614031,
