         "type" : "User",
         "url" : "https://api.github.com/users/laanwj"
      }
   },
   {
      "body" : "I think the original purpose wasn't security either, but just preventing any short read from returning meaningful data, causing a fast fail if someone would rely on the return value. That's already made impossible by the exception being thrown in the alternative (and so far, always guaranteed) case, what also explains why it's done after the throw.",
